<font color="#FF0000">WHERE DO WE GO FROM HERE?</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep  4 22:30:49 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chet,<br><br>
Healing, reflecting, considering the direction of the site.  All are reasons I have dropped from the issues of late.  I came here for a need I have not completely figured out as yet.  Mostly because of the guilt that is building from feeling no pain and very little emotion.  A casualty of events I presume.   Some I remember vividly and others seem like a dream.  A reality that I can't grasp.<br><br>
I use energy protecting friends and at the same time feel the need to include all opinions.  An almost impossible task with the emotions running so high.  I believe Doc and I arrived at a common ground which at the moment left nothing to say.<br><br>
There are no Barbarians at the gate.  We are all barbarians with our own selfish agendas and at the same time with an overwhelming need to be accepted.   Strong we think, fragile all.<br><br>
If you feel the need to go off on someone, do so.  It has been the method of us all as of late.  Sometimes it helps, if only for a moment, but always at someones else's expense.<br><br>
We have to take the good with the bad and at least achieve a net gain.  I guess we are like an emotional stock market.  We will only earn if we have the tenacity to stay.<br><br>
Someone needs to kick things off.  It appears everyone is emotionally drained.
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


